parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the power sliding doors can lead to accidents or injuries, especially when the doors open unexpectedly while driving or fail to open in emergency situations.
symptoms: The doors open or close unexpectedly
the doors fail to open or close
the door alarm sounds while driving
the doors open while driving on the highway.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities due to the loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The brakes feel spongy
the brakes fail to respond
the traction control system indicator comes on
the brakes lock up while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause a range of problems, including the malfunction of safety features, loss of control of the vehicle, and accidents.
symptoms: The horn fails to work
the keyless entry system fails
the starter gets stuck or frozen
the airbag sensor light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The key is bumped out of the ignition while driving
the vehicle stalls while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the instrument cluster can cause the driver to be unaware of important safety information, such as speed or engine performance.
symptoms: The instrument cluster needles are not illuminated when the ignition is on.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Erratic Braking and Stability Control Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unpredictable engagement of the ABS and stability control systems can cause loss of vehicle control, increased stopping distance, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle may jerk or lurch
the brakes may engage unexpectedly
the steering wheel may pull to one side
and warning lights may illuminate on the dashboard
including "Service Stability System" and "Stability Control Active".

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended activation of the brakes can cause loss of vehicle control, increased stopping distance, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: The brakes may engage unexpectedly
the vehicle may jerk or lurch
and the steering wheel may pull to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the stability control system can cause loss of vehicle control, increased stopping distance, and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: The "Service Stability System" warning light may illuminate
the vehicle may jerk or lurch
and the brakes may engage unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unintended Brake Activation and Loss of Steering Control
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended activation of the brakes and loss of steering control can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle's brakes engage unexpectedly
the steering wheel becomes difficult to turn or locks up
the vehicle pulls to one side
the ABS and traction control lights illuminate
and the vehicle may jerk or vibrate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn, leading to accidents or loss of control, especially at low speeds.
symptoms: The power steering assist suddenly fails
making the steering wheel very difficult to turn
and the failure may occur intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to shut down unexpectedly, leading to accidents or loss of control, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts down while driving or idling
the "starting disabled
reduced engine power" message appears on the display
and the vehicle may restart after a short period.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Steering Column and Tie Rod Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering column and tie rod components can cause the steering wheel to become difficult to turn or lock up, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The tie rod ends wear out prematurely
the steering wheel becomes difficult to turn
and the vehicle may vibrate or pull to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various malfunctions, including headlight flickering, starter problems, and sliding door issues, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The headlights flicker
the starter fails to engage
and the sliding door opens unexpectedly.
